    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-07-16T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-07-16T17:00:00-05:00" n="1078"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1078">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">831.00/7–1546</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Venezuela</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Corrigan</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_Niact1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                        </gloss>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-07-16T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 16, 1946—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>291. <gloss target="#t_urtel1">Urtel</gloss> 357 July 15. Pending receipt full
                        <gloss target="#t_info1">info</gloss> in <gloss target="#t_desp1"
                        >desp</gloss> referred to, Dept reiterates opinion that association with
                        <gloss target="#t_Col1">Col</gloss> most desirable particularly since latter
                    as host to López Contreras has legitimate interest and responsibility in any
                    political activities carried on by him from <gloss target="#t_Col1">Col</gloss>
                    soil. Dept appreciates possible disinclination of Betancourt to have <gloss
                        target="#t_Col1">Col</gloss> participate, but believes the over-riding
                    consideration of protecting this Govt from any possible charge intervention
                    counsels this step.</p>
                <p>Since Dawson’s trip to Medellín is not likely to escape <gloss target="#t_Col1"
                        >Col</gloss> attention, Dept considers it highly desirable that <gloss
                        target="#t_Col1">Col</gloss> Govt be informed.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Bogotá for <gloss target="#t_Amb1">Amb</gloss> and Dawson.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
